<HL>
   Business Brief -- Galveston-Houston Co.:
   Chief Executive to Resign;
   Company Will Hire Adviser
</HL>
<DATE>
04/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7A
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS GHX
</CO>
<LP>
   Galveston-Houston Co. said in Houston that its chairman,
president and chief executive officer intends to resign, and
the company plans to retain an investment banking firm to
help form a strategic plan in view of his departure.
   Nathan M. Avery has told Galveston-Houston he expects to
be nominated to serve as commercial minister to the European
Community and senior adviser to the secretary of Commerce,
the company said. If the nomination is approved, Mr. Avery
told the company he expects to assume his position in
October.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Galveston-Houston makes valve actuators and custom steel
castings for the energy and other markets.
</TEXT>
